**Build system handling:**

Cowboy uses the erlang.mk build system which by default fetches dependencies from git at build time. Since the build environment has no network access, the spec file patches out this behavior in %prep:

1. Converts `DEPS = cowlib ranch` to `LOCAL_DEPS += cowlib ranch` so erlang.mk looks for them on ERL_LIB_PATH instead of downloading
2. Removes all dep_cowlib, dep_ranch, DOC_DEPS, TEST_DEPS, and related test/CI dependency lines

In %build, ERL_LIB_PATH is set to point to system-installed cowlib and ranch packages using glob patterns (`cowlib*/ebin:ranch*/ebin`) so they are found regardless of the exact version installed.

The %install section copies the compiled .beam files into `%{erlang_libdir}/%{name}-%{version}` following openSUSE Erlang packaging conventions.

